# each prepend a release-notes entry they touch the same top-of-file region and
# git conflicts. `merge=union` (built-in driver) keeps BOTH sides' new lines
# instead of conflicting — correct for a prepend-only prose log (worst case:
# two same-session entries interleave in order, which DocIntegrity doesn't gate).
# SAFE ONLY because this file is never edited in place (no tables / no rewrites
# of existing entries — union would duplicate those). Do NOT add structured docs
# with tables here (ENGINEERING_PLAN / KNOWN_ISSUES / CODE_AUDIT stay normal-merge).
